Plan written to `plans/nodejs-github-actions-ci.plan.md`.

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The workflow uses `npm ci` instead of `npm install` -- a critical CI distinction. `npm install` can silently update `package-lock.json` if ranges resolve to newer versions; `npm ci` fails fast if the lockfile is out of sync with `package.json`, making dependency drift visible rather than hiding it. The `cache: npm` option in `actions/setup-node` keys the cache on `package-lock.json`'s hash, so cache invalidation is automatic when deps change.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

It covers 8 steps: init package.json as ESM, install devDeps, create ESLint 9 flat config, create Prettier config, add `.gitignore`, add a Vitest smoke test, create the Actions workflow, then commit each file by explicit path. Pass it to `/lz-advisor:lz-advisor-execute` when ready to implement.
